<section id="the-concept" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="the-concept">The Concept</h2>
<p>The classic Black-Scholes-Merton partial differential equation solves for a derivative’s price under strict assumptions: <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%20%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%20V%7D%7B%5Cpartial%20t%7D%20+%20%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%5Csigma%5E2%20S%5E2%20%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%5E2%20V%7D%7B%5Cpartial%20S%5E2%7D%20+%20r%20S%20%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%20V%7D%7B%5Cpartial%20S%7D%20-%20rV%20=%200%20"> Let’s quickly plot the option Greeks dynamically using Python to see how Delta changes relative to asset price.</p>
</section>
<section id="python-implementation" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="python-implementation">Python Implementation</h2>
